gold tint. It=E2=80=99s an extraordinary thing, plus Japanese art. And, of =
course, of course, the Domaine de la Roman=C3=A9e-Conti wine, which is also=
 $8,000 a bottle or so. There=E2=80=99s four bottles there by the dining ta=
ble.=E2=80=9D

Barber continued: =E2=80=9CHe took me round there, and then he said, =E2=80=
=98You can=E2=80=99t write a word about this.=E2=80=99 I=E2=80=99m thinking=
, =E2=80=98What!?=E2=80=99 So I said, =E2=80=98Why not?=E2=80=99 And he sai=
d, =E2=80=98Because no journalist has ever been in
this sanctum.=E2=80=99 And I then, without batting an eyelid, said, =E2=80=
=98But I=E2=80=99m not a journalist. I=E2=80=99m an author.=E2=80=99 Just k=
ind of cheeky, but I got away with it.=E2=80=9D

In any case, he thinks Masa liked the book well enough=E2=80=94the two ran =
into each other at the Allen & Co. conference in Sun Valley last summer and=
 chatted; Barber introduced him to his wife. Masa did ask why Barber had ca=
lled the book Gambling Man. Then he seemed to come around, musing aloud: =
=E2=80=9C=E2=80=98Gambling Man, Gambling
